rComments: Professor DeCaire makes learning a new language less intimidating. He is approachable, respectful and understanding of various levels of learning for different students. Each class, we learn something new about the language and the culture. It's important not to miss or it's easy to fall behind.

rComments: Ryan's my favorite prof at U of T. Very good teacher, gives just enough detail without giving too much and making things confusing. Makes the Mohawk language very accessible to anyone willing to put in some effort. Always kind, caring, and willing to help at any time. Highly recommend his classes.
Ryan is probably one of my favourite lecturers at U of T. He is deeply invested in your learning and only wants to help you succeed. Class is fun and something to look forward to every week!
